00:01:23.440 --> 00:01:29.040
[Amit Varma]: My topic today is the Bangladesh War of 1971, but not the events of the war itself, but

00:01:29.040 --> 00:01:32.080
[Amit Varma]: the global forces that shaped those circumstances.

00:01:32.080 --> 00:01:36.640
[Amit Varma]: People often think of the breakup of Pakistan as if it was inevitable, and people often

00:01:36.640 --> 00:01:39.960
[Amit Varma]: see it as a bilateral conflict between India and Pakistan.

00:01:39.960 --> 00:01:41.840
[Amit Varma]: None of those are quite true.

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:47.080
[Amit Varma]: Srinath Raghavan's book, 1971, A Global History of the Creation of Bangladesh, takes

00:01:47.080 --> 00:01:52.180
[Amit Varma]: a deep look at the international events that led to the creation of Bangladesh, and the

00:01:52.180 --> 00:01:58.600
[Amit Varma]: actions of not just India and Pakistan, but also the USA, the Soviet Union, and China.

